<HEADLINE> 118 Candidates Approved for Iran's Parliamentary </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, March 3 (Xinhua) -- Iran's Constitutional Guardians
Council announced on Tuesday that 118 candidates are eligible to
run in parliamentary by-election, the Iranian official news agency
IRNA reported.
</P>
<P>
The candidates will compete for five seats of the 270-member
parliament, IRNA said.
</P>
<P>
The election supervision body said it has acknowledged the
qualification of 66 candidates from Tehran, 29 from Isfahan, 17
from Khomein and six from Salmas out of the 229 applicants.
</P>
<P>
The election campaign will last for a week starting from
Thursday and the election will be held on March 13, according to
the news agency. 
</P>
</TEXT>
