<HEADLINE> Botswana Lowers Bank Rate </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, March 3 (Xinhua) -- Botswana Tuesday lowered its
bank rate to 11.75 percent from 12.0 percent, South African Press
Association quoted Botswana Central Bank as saying.
</P>
<P>
"It is now opportune to signal lower nominal interest rates in
Botswana," the bank said in a statement.
</P>
<P>
"Inflation has continued to come down steadily in 1997 and
into 1998 and it should continue to be held in check."
</P>
<P>
The bank said in the same statement that year-on-year
inflation at the end of February dropped to seven percent from
7.7 percent in January. 
</P>
