<HEADLINE> Pakistani Speaker Meets Russian Parliament Leader </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, March 3 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan and Russia have entered
a new era of friendship and close cooperation, Speaker of
Pakistan's National Assembly Ellahi Bukhsh Soomro said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Soomro told Vasily N. Likhachev, deputy chairman of the
Federation Council of Russia (upper house of parliament), that
leaders of the two countries have realized the significance of the
meaningful socio-political and economic interaction which is
mutually beneficial.
</P>
<P>
Lauding the scientific and technological progress in Russia,
Soomro said a developing country like Pakistan can and should
benefit from the transfer of technology and joint ventures with
Russia.
</P>
<P>
Likhachev, who is heading a three-member parliamentary
delegation for a visit to Pakistan, said he had extremely useful
and frank discussions with Pakistani officials on how to improve
bilateral relations in various fields.
</P>
<P>
He said Russia is keen to explore the opportunities in the
investment, energy and training sectors in Pakistan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
