<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 47 Kilograms of Pure Heroin Seized in Turkey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, March 3 (Xinhua) -- Turkish security forces seized 47
kilograms of pure heroin in an operation against drug trafficking
in eastern Turkey, the semi-official Anatolia News Agency reported
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The agency said that acting on a tip-off, the security forces
gave a "warning" to two suspected drug smugglers near Dolucikin
village of Gurpinar town of Van province at small hours Tuesday
morning and an armed clash broke out between the security forces
and the smugglers.
</P>
<P>
After the half-hour-long exchange of fire, the security forces
slightly wounded the two smugglers and confiscated the heroin on
two horses, the agency said, adding that the wounded smugglers
had been taken to Van State Hospital for treatment.
</P>
<P>
Turkey is a key transit route of drugs to Europe from the "Gold
Crescent" area overlapping Afghanistan, Pakistan and Iran. In
1996, the police seized 4.4 tonnes of heroin, or 40 percent of the
world's total haul. 
</P>
</TEXT>
