<HEADLINE> Jordan's King Hussein Visits UAE </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABU DHABI, March 3 (Xinhua) -- Jordan's King Hussein bin Talal
arrived here Wednesday afternoon on a two-day visit, the official
Wam news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
During the visit, Hussein will hold talks with president of
the United Arab Emirates (UAE) and other UAE senior officials on
"further boosting bilateral relations," the agency said.
</P>
<P>
He will also discussed with them the latest developments in
the Gulf region, in particular the accord signed between Iraq and
the United Nations last week on peacefully resolving the crisis
over U.N. arms inspections in Iraq, it added.
</P>
<P>
Wam gave no more details, but informed sources here said that
the Jordanian king will focus his discussions on improving
relations and expanding trade between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Jordan has generally been left out in the cold by the UAE and
the other Gulf countries since the 1990's Iraqi invasion of
Kuwait, because the king then sided with Baghdad.
</P>
<P>
After the 1991 Gulf war which drove Iraqi troops out of Kuwait,
Amman made effort to mend fences with the oil-rich Gulf states.
King Hussein has visited the region except Kuwait several times.
</P>
</TEXT>
