<HEADLINE> Commonwealth to Send Mission to Sierra Leone </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, March 3 (Xinhua) -- The Commonwealth announced in
London on Tuesday it would send a ministerial mission to Sierra
Leone to provide assistance in helping the West African country
recover from a recent military conflict.
</P>
<P>
It was reported that West African peace-keeping troops last
month succesfully ejected a military junta which seized power in
Sierra Leone last year.
</P>
<P>
A communique issued after a two-day meeting of Commonwealth
ministers in London said that the mission would go to Freetown as
soon as possible following the return to power of President Ahmad
Tejan Kabbah on March 10.
</P>
<P>
The mission, which will comprise representatives from Britain,
Canada, Ghana, Malaysia and Zimbabwe, would "explore ways in which
the Commonwealth could implement its resolve to assist Sierra
Leone in the task of national reconstruction and peace-building".
</P>
<P>
The Commonwealth ministers also made an urgent appeal for
providing humanitarian aid to Sierra Leone and neighbouring
countries which are housing large numbers of refugees. 
</P>
