<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Albright to Visit Canada Next Week </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, March 3 (Xinhua) -- U.S. Secretary of State Madeleine
Albright will visit Ottawa from March 9 to 10, Canadian Foreign
Affairs Minister Lloyd Axworthy announced Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
"The visit will focus on developments that have taken place in
Canada-U.S. relations since the visit of Prime Minister Jean
Chretien to Washington in April 1997," said a government news
release.
</P>
<P>
During the visit, Albright and Axworthy will discuss bilateral
issues such as Pacific salmon, environmental cooperation, and
Canada-U.S. border collaboration.
</P>
<P>
They will also exchange views on a broad range of international
issues including the United Nations, the Middle East, Nigeria,
Haiti, and the Santiago Summit to be held in April.
</P>
<P>
Albright's visit will be the first official visit to Canada of
a U.S. secretary of state in a decade, the release said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
