<HEADLINE> (rpt with correction) UN Chief Is Pleased with </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, March 3 (Xinhua) -- U.N. Secretary-General Kofi
Annan is pleased with the unanimous approval by the Security
Council of the Memorandum of Understanding he negotiated with the
Government of Iraq on February 23, UN spokesman Fred Eckhard said
on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said the Secretary-General's mission started and
finished with the consensus among the members of the Council.
</P>
<P>
Eckhard said the Secretary-General wishes to thank all those
responsible for the broad international support he received for
his diplomatic efforts from both governments and individuals.
</P>
