<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Somalia's Development a Priority for UNDP </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, March 3 (Xinhua) -- The United Nations
Development Program (UNDP) will call on donors from the Arab
World and other regions to mobilize resources for Somalia, a
release from UNDP said on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Fawaz Fokeladeh, director of UNDP's Regional Bureau for the
Arab States, told Somalian faction leaders during a visit to the
country earlier last month that he will do all he can to encourage
Arab countries to release more funding for development projects in
Somalia.
</P>
<P>
"There are some countries that will be given high priority from
us, and Somalia is one of them," he said.
</P>
<P>
In Mogadishu, he met with three faction leaders to discuss
their plans to set up a joint administration for the city and
surrounding areas.
</P>
<P>
Somalia has no central government for more than six years.
</P>
</TEXT>
