<DOCNO> XIE19980304.0051 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-03 20:20 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Iran Rejects US Criticism of Anti-drug Efforts </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, March 3 (Xinhua) -- Iran on Tuesday rejected the
criticism of the United States that it has not been fully
cooperative in stopping international drug trafficking.
</P>
<P>
The Anti-narcotics Campaign Headquarters issued a statement
saying the United Nations and the International Police have
confirmed and lauded Iran's measures in combating drug smuggling.
</P>
<P>
"Any judgement regarding the anti-narcotics measures by
countries should be done by international organizations," the
statement said, quoted by Iran's official news agency IRNA.
</P>
<P>
U.S. Secretary of State Madeleine Albright, though terming
Iran's anti-drug efforts as "encouraging" on Thursday, said it has
not been cooperating fully to stop international drug shipment.
</P>
<P>
The statement said that Iran has spent 350 million U.S. dollars
to cut off narcotics transit routes in the eastern frontiers and
built walls along its borders with Afghanistan and Pakistan, where
the drugs was planted, harvested and processed.
</P>
<P>
Evidences have showed Iran's political resolves to combat
narcotics and drug trafficking, the statement argued.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Iranian anti-drug officials have said that Iran has
captured an average of 160 tonnes of various narcotics each year
over the last years.
</P>
<P>
Iran is one of the key routes used by traffickers to ship drugs
produced in the "Golden Crescent" overlapping Iran, Pakistan and
Afghanistan to Europe, and it has witnessed a serious social
problem triggered by drug abuses.
</P>
<P>
To tighten the screw on drug smuggling, Iran passed a strict
anti-drug law in January 1989 to slap the death penalty to those
who are caught with 30 grams of heroin or five kilograms of opium.
</P>
<P>
Reports have said that more than 3,000 drug smugglers have been
executed and hundreds of thousands of drug addicts jailed in Iran
since the law took effect. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
