<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-03 20:27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> French President Special Envoy Arrives in Baghdad </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BAGHDAD, March 3 (Xinhua) -- French president's special envoy
Bertrand Dufourq arrived here Tuesday evening on his second
visit to Baghdad within a month to outline the importance of
implementing the agreement on arms inspection.
</P>
<P>
Dufourq, general secretary of French foreign ministry, told
reporters upon arrival at Saddam internation Airport that he
would deliver a letter from President Jacques Chirac to
President Saddam Hussein.
</P>
<P>
He said he would discuss with Iraqi officials on the
importance of full implementation of the agreement signed by
U.N. Secretary-General Kofi Annan and Iraq on February 23.
</P>
<P>
The U.N. Security Council adopted a resolution on Monday
which approves the agreement and warns of the "severest
consequences" if Iraq violates the agreement.
</P>
<P>
Dufourq visited Baghdad as French president's special envoy
early last month to find a diplomatic solution to the then
standoff between Iraq and the United States over U.N. weapons
inspection.
</P>
<P>
France had played an important role in blocking a U.S.-led air
strike on Iraq and engineering the U.N.-Iraq accord on resuming
inspections for weapons of mass destruction in Iraq. 
</P>
</TEXT>
