<HEADLINE> Black-Owned Group Buys S. Africa's Biggest Wine </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, March 3 (Xinhua) -- South Africa's black-owned
Maluti Foods and Beverages has signed a 30-million-Rand (six
million U.S. Dollars) pact to buy the biggest wine producer and
wholesaler, Stellenbosch Farmers Winery (SFW), in the country.
</P>
<P>
The agreement, the biggest black empowerment deal in the wine
industry, will be funded by SFW, with Maluti repaying the debt
over 12 years in the form of 80 percent of grapes harvested once
full production is reached, South African Press Association
reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
SFW Managing Director Frans Stroebel described the deal signed
in Cape Town as historic, adding that to embrace
previously-disadvantaged communities was the only way the wine
industry could survive in new South Africa. 
</P>
</TEXT>
