<HEADLINE> LIFFE Trades 17,491,896 Contracts in February </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, March 3 (Xinhua) -- The London International Financial
Futures and Options Exchange (LIFFE) traded 17,491,896 futures and
options contracts last month, according to figures released
Tuesday by the exchange.
</P>
<P>
Average daily volume amounted to 874,595 futures and options
contracts, representing an average daily nominal turnover of
206.53 billion pounds (338.70 billion U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
The LIFFE said that since the beginning of the year, it has
traded 38,299,022 futures and options contracts as against
34,757,306 in the same period in 1997, an increase of 10 percent.
Average daily nominal turnover increased by 18 percent from 174.83
billion pounds (286.72 billion dollars) in February 1997.
</P>
<P>
LIFFE Chief Executive Daniel Hodson said, "Following a record
January, February has been yet another high volume month. As we
move towards European Economic and Monetary Union in January 1999,
there is increasing interest in short term interest rate futures
(STIRS), with volumes up 47 percent this year."
</P>
<P>
He added that the LIFFE is dominated in the STIRS area,
increasing its market share of European STIR contracts from 81
percent a year ago to 90 percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
