<HEADLINE> Hungary Calls for Restraint Over Kosovo Crisis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUDAPEST, March 4 (Xinhua) -- Hungary Wednesday urged the
conflicting parties in the recent ethnic violence in Yugoslavia's
autonomous province of Kosovo to exercise restraint.
</P>
<P>
Only through negotiations can the conflict have a peaceful and
permanent end, and the possibility to resolve the crisis lies
inside Yugoslavia, said a Foreign Ministry statement.
</P>
<P>
Condemning the violence in Kosovo, the statement said Hungary,
as a neighbor of Yugoslavia, wishes stability in the region.
</P>
<P>
Tension in Kosovo heightened on March 1 after an escalation of
armed conflict between Serbian police and ethnic Albanians, during
which four policemen and 16 Albanians were killed, and two other
policemen injured.
</P>
<P>
Ethnic Albanians, who account for 90 percent of the population
in Kosovo, have been seeking independence from Yugoslavia since
1981. 
