<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Capable to Cope with Complex Economic Situation: Zhu Rongji </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 4 (Xinhua) -- The Communist Party of China's
collective leadership with Jiang Zemin at the core is fully
capable to cope with various complicated situation in national
economic development, Vice-Premier Zhu Rongji said here today.
</P>
<P>
Zhu made the remarks when referring to the financial crisis in
some Asian countries and the Chinese government's measures to
avoid the negative impact to China in a panel discussion with
members of the Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference
(CPPCC), China's top advisory body.
</P>
<P>
China can maintain the good momentum of steady, fast and
healthy economic growth as long as it can "earnestly implement the
various principles and policies already defined by the CPC Central
Committee and the State Council", said the vice-premier, who is
also a member of the Standing Committee of the Political Bureau of
the Chinese Communist Party Central Committee.
</P>
<P>
Joining discussion with members of the on-going First Session
of the Ninth CPPCC National Committee this afternoon, Zhu also
briefed the members on China's current economic situation.
</P>
<P>
In the panel discussion, CPPCC National Committee members from
the economic circles set forth a number of proposals on the
country's macro-economic control, infrastructure construction,
readjustment of industrial structure and prevention of financial
risks.
</P>
<P>
Other members also touched on such subjects as the reform of
the state-owned enterprises, the re-employment program and the
issue concerning redundant construction. 
</P>
