<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Achieves Economic Growth Goals for 1997 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 4 (Xinhua) -- China achieved its overall 1997
economic objective of "seeking development through stability".
</P>
<P>
The State Statistical Bureau issued a communique today outlining
national economic and social development during 1997.
</P>
<P>
Official statistics show the 1997 gross domestic product
(GDP) hit 7,477.2 billion yuan (901.2 billion US dollars), up 8.8
percent on the previous year.
</P>
<P>
The value-added of the primary industry stood at 1,367.4 billion
yuan, up 3.5 percent on 1996, with the
sector's share of GDP dropping by 1.9 percentage points.
</P>
<P>
The value-added of the seconded industry ended at 3,677 billion
yuan, up 10.8 percent, with its share of GDP growing by 0.2
percentage points.
</P>
<P>
The value-added of the tertiary industry jumped 8.2
percent to 2,432.8 billion yuan, with a 1.7 percentage point rise in
the sector's share of GDP.
</P>
<P>
</P>
</TEXT>
