<HEADLINE> Garment Industry Earns 70 Percent of Bangladesh </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, March 4 (Xinhua) -- Bangladesh's garment industry
contributes more than 70 percent to the country's export earnings,
Mostafa Golam Quddus, the newly-elected president of the
Bangladesh Garment Manufacturers and Exporters Association
(BGMEA), said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The industry, which employs some 1.4 million workers, generates
the most job opportunities in the country, Quddus told reporters.
</P>
<P>
About 90 percent of the employees in the industry are women,
fostering women's empowerment and emancipation, he said.
</P>
<P>
There are about 2,600 garment factories in Bangladesh and they
are mainly located in the capital city of Dhaka, Narayanganj,
almost 20 kilometers south of the capital, and Chittagong in the
southeast of the country, M. M. Jahangir, secretary of BGMEA, told
reporters.
</P>
<P>
Most of the garments produced in Bangladesh are exported to
North America and Europe, he said.
</P>
<P>
In the 1996-97 fiscal year which ended on June 30, 1997, the
garment industry earned some 3.4 billion U.S. dollars out of the
country's total export earnings of 4.4 billion dollars.  
</P>
</TEXT>
