<HEADLINE> Kuwait, Egyptian to Sign Trade Agreement </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, March 4 (Xinhua) -- Kuwait and Egypt are to sign a
trade agreement and a memorandum of understanding on economic and
trade cooperation, a Kuwaiti official said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Kuwait's Assistant Trade and Industry Undersecretary Bader
Abdelrahim was quoted by Kuwait News Agency as saying that the two
countries would sign a trade agreement to cancel tariffs between
the two countries within five years during a visit to Kuwait by
Egyptian Minister of Supply and Trade Ahmad Al-Gowailia scheduled
for April 20.
</P>
<P>
He said the aim of the agreement is to speed up the liberation
of trade from restrictions and tariffs.
</P>
<P>
The agreement includes a protocol to deal with several
technical issues like manufacturing, the quality of the products
and methods of calculating the additional value, he added.
</P>
<P>
Bilateral trade between Kuwait and Egypt has been an important
part in the their inter-Arab trade fields. In 1996, Kuwaiti
imports from Egypt reached 22.7 million Kuwaiti Dinars (74.9
million U.S. dollars), while exports to Egypt totaled 5.228
million Kuwaiti Dinars (17.25 million U.S. dollars) except of oil
and its derivatives.
</P>
<P>
The Egyptian minister will also sign during his visit a
memo of cooperation, coordination and exchanging experts and
information in the economic and trade negotiations within the
framework of international organizations and regional meetings,
Abdelrahim said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
