<HEADLINE> People's Daily Editorial Hails Opening of NPC Session (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 4 (Xinhua) -- The Thursday edition of the
People's Daily, China's leading newspaper, will carry an editorial
hailing the opening of the First Session of the Ninth National
People's Congress (NPC), China's top legislature.
</P>
<P>
The article, titled "Looking forward into the future and striving
for new achievements," describes the NPC session as "another
major event in China's political life" following the 15th National
Congress of the Communist Party of China (CPC) convened last
September.
</P>
<P>
It points out that this year's NPC session is an important one
since it will hear and examine a government work report and other
important reports, discuss and approve a plan of institutional
restructuring to be submitted by the State Council, and elect or
confirm new leaders of the central authorities.
</P>
<P>
"This session will hold high the great banner of Deng Xiaoping
Theory, turn the magnificent goal set by the 15th National Party
Congress for China's development into state will, and provide
effective political and organizational guarantees for further
mobilizing the Chinese people to strive for an all-round
advancement of the cause of building socialism with Chinese
characteristics into the 21st century," it says.
</P>
<P>
It notes that the past five years since the First Session of
the Eighth NPC have witnessed remarkable successes for China's
reform, opening-up and socialist modernization drive.
</P>
<P>
"Experience of the five years has proved that Deng Xiaoping
Theory and the Party's basic line are great guidelines for our
nation's prosperity and advancement, that the Party Central
Committee with Jiang Zemin at the core is a strong, powerful and
diligent collective leadership with pioneering spirit, and that
intimacy and unity between various ethnic groups across the
country are a basic guarantee for the success of various causes,"
it comments.
</P>
</TEXT>
