<HEADLINE> People's Daily Editorial Hails Opening of NPC Session (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
It says that in the past five years, people's congresses at all
levels, along with their standing committees, have exercised their
powers according to law, made great efforts to improve China's
democracy and legal system, and played a vital role in various
aspects of the Chinese society.
</P>
<P>
It praises the people's congress system as "a great
creation" by Mao Zedong and other Chinese revolutionary veterans
by combining the basic theory of Marxism with China's specific
conditions.
</P>
<P>
"Practice in nearly half a century since the founding of New
China and in the two decades of reform and opening-up has proved
that the people's congress system is a good system which suits
Chinese realities, promotes national prosperity and makes the
Chinese people owners of their country," it says.
</P>
<P>
It goes on to say that the next five years, which will be the
term of office for the Ninth NPC, are of critical importance for
China's development.
</P>
<P>
"Since 1998 is the first year for us to implement the
guidelines of the 15th National Party Congress, we have extremely
arduous tasks in reform and development this year, with many
problems and difficulties to solve and overcome. Our performance
in 1998 will have a significant impact on the next few years,"
says the article.
</P>
<P>
Therefore, it says, it is necessary to further expand socialist
democracy, improve the socialist legal system, uphold and develop
the people's congress system, and take effective measures to
guarantee democracy in elections, decision-making, management and
supervision.
</P>
<P>
"Only by so doing can we bring people's wisdom and strength
into full play and mobilize them to strive for the attainment of
our goals," it says. 
</P>
