<HEADLINE> Fujian-Taiwan Automobile Joint Venture Operating Smoothly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, March 4 (Xinhua) -- The Southeast Automobile Industry
Co. Ltd., a joint venture between east China's Fujian Province and
Taiwan, has reported a successful operation.
</P>
<P>
Sources with the company said that its first product, the
"Delica" mini-van, has become a domestic automobile brand-name.
</P>
<P>
So far, the joint venture has the capacity to produce 10,000
Delica vans annually through 38 sales outlets with 43 specialized
maintenance centers nationwide. In response to the market demand,
Southeast has introduced a series of new products including a
postal car, ambulance, police car and cash carrier. Last year, the
sales of these specialized vehicles topped 2,730 units.
</P>
<P>
Southeast has chosen a new site in the province's Qingkou
Investment Zone to expand component production. Construction has
been finished on the upcoming factories.
</P>
<P>
The joint venture was approved by the State Planning Commission
in July. An initial investment of 99.8 million U.S. dollars was
required on a 50-50 basis.
</P>
<P>
The Taiwan partner, the Yulong Group, is the largest automobile
producer on the island, which has secured half of the Taiwan auto
market. Its investment in Fujian Province has flowed to the
production of ready vehicles, auto parts and components, and
engines. It has also helped set up automobile research and
development centers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
