<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hong Kong NPC Deputy Pledges to Perform Duty </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 4 (Xinhua) -- "I will try to be worthy of the
trust Hong Kong people have placed in me and work together with
other deputies to the Ninth National People's Congress (NPC) to
perform our sacred duties," a Hong Kong deputy to the Ninth NPC
said here today.
</P>
<P>
This sentiment was expressed by Deputy Ng Chack-tim.
</P>
<P>
"I think the current NPC session is of special significance for
Hong Kong deputies because all the deputies from the Hong Kong
Special Administrative Region (HKSAR) were elected by an electoral
body entirely composed of Hong Kong residents and Hong Kong
deputies have formed an independent delegation for the first time
for the coming session of the NPC," said Ng, who is head of the
Hong Kong delegation to the Ninth NPC First Session which is to
open here tomorrow.
</P>
<P>
As a deputy to the fifth, sixth, seventh and eighth
NPCs, Ng has witnessed how China has
traveled from chaos to stability and prosperity.
</P>
<P>
"I feel a great honor to be a deputy elected by Hong Kong
residents and have a strong sense of having returned to the
embrace of the motherland," Ng said.
</P>
<P>
"All the deputies from the HKSAR are fully aware of their
responsibilities as people all over the world will follow closely
how we participate in the deliberation and administration of state
affairs," he said.
</P>
<P>
The First Session of the Ninth NPC is of great significance for
China's reform and further development, he said, since the session
will turn the blueprint worked out at the 15th National Congress of
the Communist Party of China (CPC) into a program of action.
</P>
<P>
He said deputies from Hong Kong have their own advantages.
Since Hong Kong is an international financial, trade and
information center, Hong Kong deputies have a better idea of the
rules and characteristics of a market economy, are well informed
and lively in thinking, he said.
</P>
<P>
"This has made it possible for them to raise constructive
ideas and proposals, thereby contributing to reform and the
establishment of a socialist market economy in interior areas,"
he said.
</P>
<P>
"I'm confident of the success of the congress session," he
said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
