<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shanghai Sets Up Human Genome Research Center </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, March 4 (Xinhua) -- The Shanghai Human Genome
Research Center, a major genetic research institution in China,
was established here today.
</P>
<P>
Approved by the State Science and Technology Commission, the
research center will mainly engage in the study of how to separate
the gene relating to human disease from the functional gene, the
establishment of a gene-testing system and the study of the
biotics relating to human genome.
</P>
<P>
In the near future, the center will strive to establish an
experimental system on the study of the structure and function of
human genomes, and explore genes relating to such main diseases in
China as liver ailments, leukemia, angiocardiopathy and diabetes.
</P>
<P>
The research center was organized by the China National Center
for Bio-engineering Development and the Shanghai Science and
Technology Commission as well as universities, research
institutions, hospitals and enterprises in Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
Attending today's ceremony to mark the establishment of the
center were Huang Ju, a member of the Political Bureau of the
Central Committee of the Communist Party of China (CPC) and
secretary of the CPC Shanghai Committee; and Shanghai Mayor Xu
Kuangdi.  
</P>
</TEXT>
