<HEADLINE> Shanghai Stock Exchange Has Sluggish Trading in February </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, March 4 (Xinhua) -- The Shanghai Stock Exchange
(SSE), one of two in China, experienced sluggish trading in
February compared with the previous month.
</P>
<P>
The average daily stock transaction was down 23 percent from
January to 3.9 billion yuan. The monthly turnover was 59.95 billion
yuan.
</P>
<P>
The Comprehensive Index closed the month at 1,206.53 points,
a slight rise of 1.3 points over the previous month.
</P>
<P>
Sales of Hongqiao Airport stock, listed on the SSE with 270
million A-shares on Feb. 18, were sluggish consistent with the
overall decline.
</P>
<P>
Affected by Hong Kong's stock market, B-share trading was
active, ending at 58.73, surging 24.73 points over the previous
month. Total transactions posted were 1.2 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
State bond trading remained brisk with the turnover of spot
trading topping 37.54 billion yuan. The earnings ratio of the
repurchased bonds was poised at 8 percent and its February
transaction volume reached 76.19 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, SSE funds trading was bearish with its monthly
turnover sloping down to 757 million yuan.  
</P>
