<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Progress in Fujian-Taiwan Economic Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 4 (Xinhua) -- A growing number of Taiwan
industrialists have invested in the past few years in east China's
Fujian Province where the investment environment has kept
improving.
</P>
<P>
In 1997, Fujian approved 456 Taiwan-funded projects involving
1.2 billion U.S. dollars of investment from Taiwan, a 89-percent
rise over the previous year, said Zhang Jiakun, a deputy to the
Ninth National People's Congress. Zhang is here to attend the
NPC's first session due to open tomorrow.
</P>
<P>
More than 5,000 Taiwan-funded projects have been built in
Fujian since 1983 and businesses from Taiwan have actually
invested a total of 5.6 billion US dollars in Fujian, according to
Zhang, who is also vice-governor of Fujian.
</P>
<P>
Owing to the fact that more large Taiwan enterprises have come
to Fujian to invest, average investment from Taiwan in each
Taiwan-funded project increased from less than 1 million US
dollars in 1988 to 5.9 million U.S. dollars in 1996, said Weng
Fulin, who is mayor of Fuzhou as well as an NPC deputy.
</P>
<P>
Also, Taiwan investors have started more than 1,000
agricultural projects in Fujian involving close to 1 billion US
dollars in Taiwan investment money, according to Zhang Jiakun.
</P>
