<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Education Makes Steady Development </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 4 (Xinhua) -- China's education made steady
development in 1997, the State Statistics Bureau announced here
today.
</P>
<P>
China now has 1,020 general universities with 3.17 million
enrolled undergraduate students, including one million new
entrants; 735 universities and institutions that offer courses
leading to postgraduate degrees, ao 180,000 enroled graduate
students, including 64,000 new entrants.
</P>
<P>
Pupils enrolled in primary schools numbered 139.95 million in
1997, bringing the enrollment rate of primary-school-age children
to 98.9 percent.
</P>
<P>
A total of 4.04 million people completed basic literacy courses
in 1997, noted the bureau. 
</P>
</TEXT>
