<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Witnesses Big Growth in Retail Sales of Consumer Goods </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 4 (Xinhua) -- Market of commodities remained
stable under a buyer-oriented pattern in 1997, said a report
released today by State Statistics Bureau.
</P>
<P>
According to the report, the total retail sales of consumer
goods was 2,684.3 billion yuan, up 11.1 percent over the previous
year, with a real growth of 10.2 percent if price factor was
deducted.
</P>
<P>
In terms of urban and rural areas, the retail sales of consumer
goods in urban areas reached 1,639.5 billion yuan, a real growth
of 10.9 percent, and the retail sales of consumer goods at and
below county level was 1,044.9 billion yuan, up by 9.2 percent.
</P>
<P>
In terms of different ownership, the retail sales of
state-owned (including controlled share owned by the state)
outlets was 724.8 billion yuan; that of collective outlets was
488.8 billion yuan; private outlets, 99.0 billion yuan; and
outlets of other forms of ownership, 398.2 billion yuan,
representing an increase of 4.3 percent, 7.1 percent, 25.1 percent
and 13.6 percent respectively over that in the previous year.
</P>
<P>
In terms of different industries, the retail sales of the
wholesale and retail trades was up 9.2 percent and the retail
sales of the catering industry was up 18.5 percent. The supply at
the market for means of production was ample, and their prices
remained stable with slight decline.
</P>
<P>
The total sales of means of production was 1,914.2 billion
yuan, up by 4.5 percent. Transactions at fair markets were brisk,
the total volume of business was 1,742.5 billion yuan, up by 18.6
percent over the previous year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
