<HEADLINE> Cultural Undertakings Make Progress in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 4 (Xinhua) -- China's cultural and art
undertakings has made further progress, according to the State
Statistics Bureau.
</P>
<P>
On a press conference held here today, the bureau said that
there were 2,563 art-performing groups, 3,097 culture centers,
2,690 public libraries and 1,218 museums in the country by the end
of 1997.
</P>
<P>
A total of 744 medium and short-wave radio transmitting and
relaying stations throughout China brought radio programs to 85.8
percent of the total population and 1,295 TV transmitting and
relaying stations, each with a capacity of over 1,000 watts)
covered 87.4 percent of the total population.
</P>
<P>
During the year, China produced 88 feature movies and
distributed 373 movies (including redistributions) on domestic
market and 126 movies on overseas markets.
</P>
<P>
It also published 19.3 billion copies of newspapers, 2.5
billion copies of magazines and 7.1 billion copies of books at the
national and provincial level. Plus, 29.40 million documents were
made accessible to the public. 
