<HEADLINE> China Reports Increasing Efficiency From Construction Industry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 4 (Xinhua) -- The construction industry of China
continued to develop steadily with improved economic efficiency in
1997, said a report released today by the State Statistics Bureau.
</P>
<P>
The value added of the state-owned construction enterprises was
133.4 billion yuan in 1997, up 2.6 percent over the previous year.
</P>
<P>
The total number of projects under construction was 220,000, of
which, 88,000 were constructed through bidding system, accounting
for 39.6 percent of the total, or 5.6 percentage points higher
than that in the previous year.
</P>
<P>
Floor space of buildings completed during the past year was 156
million square meters, down by 19 million square meters.
Forty-five percent of completed construction projects was rated
quality projects, 1.5 percentage points higher than in 1996. The
total profits and taxes made was 15.2 billion yuan in 1997, an
increase of 8.7 percent over 1996, said the report. 
</P>
</TEXT>
