<BODY>
<HEADLINE> ECOMOG Captures Makeni in Northern S. Leone </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, March 4 (Xinhua) -- The West Africa peace-keeping force
known as ECOMOG has captured Makeni, a provincial capital town in
northern Sierra Leone, reports reaching here said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The reports said the ECOMOG met no resistance from troops
loyal to ousted military junta leader Major Johnny Paul Koromah,
who had fled before the ECOMOG entered the town Monday evening.
</P>
<P>
ECOMOG troops took Sierra Leonean capital Freetown on February
12, forcing Koromah and his junta members to flee.
</P>
<P>
Since then, the peace-keepers have seized Bo, a major city in
the south, the diamond-producing Kenema in the heartland and iron
ore mining center Hunsar.
</P>
<P>
As ECOMOG is consolidating its control over most part of
Sierra Leone, President Ahmed Tejan Kabbah, who was toppled by
Koromah in a coup last May and has since in exile in neighboring
Guinea, is expected to return to Freetown to resume power on
March 10.
</P>
<P>
International aid has also begun to come in. 
</P>
</TEXT>
