<HEADLINE> China Increases Technology Input </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 4 (Xinhua) -- China's scientific and technical
personnel continued to grow in size in 1997, according to the
State Statistics Bureau today.
</P>
<P>
At a press conference here today, the bureau
announced that the country has had 29.14 million professionals and
technicians of all specialization by the end of 1997, an increase
of 0.4 percent over the figure in 1996.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, some 82,000 foreign experts worked in China in the
year, up 2.5 percent.
</P>
<P>
Financial input into this sector also increased, noted
statistics.
</P>
<P>
The expenditure on scientific and technological activities of
research institutions, universities and large and medium-sized
industrial and construction enterprises in 1997 was 96.1 billion
yuan, up 8.6 percent.
</P>
<P>
Of the total, expenditure on research and development was 36.8
billion yuan, up 10.4 percent. The figure accounted for 0.5
percent of the country's gross domestic product (GDP) in the
year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
