<HEADLINE> Ramos: Philippine-Brunei Relations to Deepen </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, March 4 (Xinhua) -- President Fidel Ramos expressed
confidence here on Wednesday that the visit of Brunei Sultan Haji
Hassanal Bolkiah to the Philippines will boost the ties between
the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Ramos, who described the bilateral relations as "close and
fraternal," said in a statement that the visit would provide
impetus for the expansion and deepening of partnership between
Brunei and the Philippines.
</P>
<P>
"Our political, economic and socio-cultural ties continue to
vigorously expand at the bilateral level and in the context of our
close cooperation within the ASEAN (the Association of Southeast
Asian Nations)," Ramos said.
</P>
<P>
The President said he looks forward to the opportunity to
interact with the Sultan and his delegation during the three-day
visit starting March 4.
</P>
<P>
Sultan Bolkiah will arrive here Wednesday evening. He would
hold talks with President Ramos during the visit. 
</P>
