<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Industrial Production Growing Steadily </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 4 (Xinhua) -- China's industrial production kept
steady growth in 1997 with the added value reaching 3.1752
trillion yuan, up by 11.1 percent over the previous year,
announced today by the State Statistics Bureau.
</P>
<P>
Of the total, the added value created by the state-owned
enterprises and joint-ownership enterprises where the state held
the controlling share registered 1.1726 trillion yuan, up 7.1
percent.
</P>
<P>
The added value created by enterprises of other types of
ownership such as joint-ventures, cooperative enterprises and
foreign-funded enterprises reached 445 billion yuan, up 13.4
percent.
</P>
<P>
And that of urban and rural individual enterprises was 553.3
billion yuan, up 18.1 percent.
</P>
<P>
Of the total added industrial value, the share produced by
light industry registered 1.468 trillion yuan, up 11.7 percent,
and by heavy industry, 1.7072 trillion, up 10.5 percent.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
