<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Germany to Promote Relations with Namibia, S. </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, March 4 (Xinhua) -- German President Roman
Herzog is due to meet his Namibian counterpart Sam Nujoma in
Windhoek to boost ties with the country Wednesday, informed
sources reaching here said.
</P>
<P>
It will be Herzog's first tour of Southern Africa since he
became head of state four years ago.
</P>
<P>
Germany is the most important trade partner for the former
German colony which was under South African rule until it gained
independence in 1990.
</P>
<P>
During his eigh-day trip, Herzog will also fly Sunday to South
Africa, Germany's biggest trade partner in Africa, with bilateral
trade totalling about five billion U.S. Dollars.
</P>
<P>
During his stay in South Africa, Herzong will hold talks with
South African President Nelson Mandela, Deputy President Thabo
Mbeki and is to address a special sitting of parliament in Cape
Town, said officials of the Department of Foreign Affairs.
</P>
<P>
During the visit, a number of bilateral agreements on
environmental cooperation, cultural matters, air and maritime
transport, an update on double taxation avoidance and financial
cooperation on low-cost housing will also be signed, they said.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
