<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Vietnam Thanks WMO for Meteorological Aid </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, March 4 (Xinhua) -- Vietnam thanked the World
Meteorological Organization (WMO) for its aid and hoped that it
could do more, a Vietnam official said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Nguyen Duc Ngu, General Director of the General Department of
Meteorology and Hydrology, did this when meeting with
visiting WMO Secretary General G.O.P. Obasi.
</P>
<P>
Ngu specifically mentioned WMO's assistance and cooperation
through WMO-funded projects in providing Vietnam with modern
equipments and personnel training.
</P>
<P>
These projects have helped Vietnam implement its
social-economic development programs, Ngu stressed.
</P>
<P>
Vietnam, however, needs more WMO aid to increase its
effectiveness in weather forecasts to mitigate the affects of
natural calamities, he said.
</P>
<P>
Obasi is on his week-long visit here beginning from Monday.
He visited Vietnam in 1990 at the head of a high-level MWO
delegation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
