<DOCNO> XIE19980304.0189 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> NPC Spokesman On Human Rights </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 4 (Xinhua) -- An NPC session spokesman argued
for China's human rights record today, saying China has signed
altogether 17 international conventions on human rights, "two more
than the United States which has signed only 15."
</P>
<P>
Spokesman Zeng Jianhui said at a press conference today the
Chinese government has made great efforts to protect its people's
civil rights and enacted a series of laws and regulations for the
purpose.
</P>
<P>
The revised criminal law, the law on criminal procedures and
the lawyers law provide legal protection for people having trouble
with the law, he said.
</P>
<P>
Also, he gave high credit to China's electoral system, saying
that it is consistent with the country's realities and "represents
true democracy."
</P>
<P>
He said direct election of deputies to people's congresses at
county and township levels has been practised nationwide.
Moreover, multi-candidate elections are widely used, he said.
</P>
<P>
"Facts have proved that our electoral system has effectively
guaranteed people's rights as masters of their own country, and
the system has won their full support," Zeng said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
