<HEADLINE> China's Market Price Move with Minor Fluctuation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 4 (Xinhua) -- China's retail prices of
commodities in 1997 rose by 0.8 percent over the previous year
with their growth rate dropped by 5.3 percentage points, the State
Statistics Bureau announced today.
</P>
<P>
The consumer prices of households went up by 2.8 percent, with
their growth rate down by 5.5 percentage points.
</P>
<P>
This was attributed mainly to rational macro-economic policies
and to the consecutive harvest in agriculture.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, a buyer-oriented market has taken shape. The
strengthened role of market mechanism has also played a positive
role to some extent in curbing the price increase. 
</P>
</TEXT>
