<HEADLINE> China's Unemployment Rate Registers 3.1 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 4 (Xinhua) -- China's urban unemployment rate
registered 3.1 percent at the end of 1997, or 0.1 percentage point
higher than at the end of 1996, the State Statistics Bureau
announced today.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the total of employed people in China numbered 696
million at the end of 1997, or 7.5 million more than at the end of
1996.
</P>
<P>
Of this total, 147.6 million were staffs and workers in urban
areas, a decrease of 850,000 persons over that at the end of 1996.
</P>
<P>
It said that some 26.69 million people were employed in private
enterprises or self-employed in urban areas and 4.8 million
laid-off workers found new jobs through various channels.
</P>
