<HEADLINE> Statistics on China's Industrial Sectors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 4 (Xinhua) -- China's primary industry saw its
value-added increase by 3.5 percent to reach 1.3674 trillion yuan
in 1997, the State Statistics Bureau announced today.
</P>
<P>
At the same time, its share in GDP dropped by 1.9 percentage
points, the Bureau said.
</P>
<P>
The added value of the secondary industry registered 3.677
trillion yuan, up by 10.8 percent, and its share rose by 0.2
percentage points in 1997.
</P>
<P>
And the added value of the tertiary industry was 2.4328
trillion yuan, up by 8.2 percent, with its share in GDP growing by
1.7 percentage points last year.  
</P>
