<HEADLINE> China's Foreign Exchange Reserve Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 4 (Xinhua) -- China's foreign exchange reserve
reached 139.9 billion US dollars at the end of 1997, an increase
of 34.9 billion as compared with that in 1996, the State
Statistics Bureau announced today.
</P>
<P>
The country's situation of international balance of payment was
favorable, characterized by surplus in both current accounts and
capital accounts.
</P>
<P>
The exchange rate of the Chinese currency, RMB, remained stable
with slight appreciation, rising from one US dollar equal to
8.2984 RMB yuan at the beginning of 1997 to one US dollar equal to
8.2796 RMB yuan at the end of the year, an appreciation of 188
basic points. 
</P>
</TEXT>
