<HEADLINE> Beihai Expects Fast Economic Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 4 (Xinhua) -- Beihai, a coastal city in south
China's Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region, has entered a period of
steady economic growth, a senior party official from the city said
here today.
</P>
<P>
The opening to traffic of the Naning-Kuming railway has given
an impetus to the development of Beihai, said Cen Hongping, a
deputy to the Ninth National People's Congress and secretary of
the Beihai Municipal Committee of the Communist Party of China
(CPC), who is here to attend the first session of the Ninth NPC.
</P>
<P>
Preferential treatments granted to Guangxi by the Central
Government and rich marine and tourist resources make Beihai a
hot spot for overseas and domestic investment, he said.
</P>
<P>
A number of multinational corporations have recently signed
investment contracts worth billions of US dollars with the city,
he said.
</P>
<P>
Work on a thermo-power plant costing 8 billion yuan has started
this year; a project for separating oil from gas has started
operation; and a project to expand the Beihai Airport is near
completion, he said.
</P>
<P>
The property market, generally acknowledged as a barometer of
economic performance, is fast recovering in Beihai. Prices on the
local real estate market have soared 30 percent and the number of
apartment purchases has doubled this year, he said.
</P>
<P>
The city played host to 2.6 million Chinese and overseas
tourists last year, up 40 percent over the previous year. The
tourist market this year is booming, he said.
</P>
<P>
High-tech, information and service industries have also
developed rapidly in recent years in Beihai, he said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
