<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Jiang Zemin, Li Ruihuan Join Scientists in Panel Discussions </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 4 (Xinhua) -- President Jiang Zemin and senior
official of the Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference
(CPPCC) Li Ruihuan this morning joined some scientists
attending the ongoing First Session of the Ninth CPPCC National
Committee in their panel discussions.
</P>
<P>
After listening to speeches of scientists, Jiang Zemin, also
general secretary of the Communist Party of China (CPC) Central
Committee, said that at the turn of the century science and
technology are playing an increasingly bigger role in economic
expansion around the world.
</P>
<P>
The trend highlights a rapid momentum of new and high
technologies with information technology as the key sector, closer
combination of economy and science and technology, new production
management and organization as the result of a new
technology-economy system, and greater attention to fostering
scientific and technological personnel, Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
"Facing such a situation, all countries, big nations in
particular, are losing no time to map out their development
strategies geared to the 21st century," Jiang Zemin said.
</P>
<P>
"We must have a profound assessment of the great impact of
science and technology, especially high technology, on the overall
national strength, social and economic structure and the people's
life," he said.
</P>
<P>
He called on scientists to be fully aware of both challenge and
opportunity brought about by the new technology revolution so as
to boost China's science and technology. Without scientific and
technological innovations, the national economy will be subjected
to others' control, and the economic gap cannot be narrowed.
</P>
<P>
The Communist Party and government have been placing great
emphasis on the promotion of scientific and technological
advancement, Jiang said, adding that since the reform and
opening-up was initiated, a series of correct policies for
revitalizing the country with science and education have been
worked out.
</P>
<P>
In this sense, the president underlined the combination of
economy and science and technology, the development of both basic
and high-tech researches, and a proper selection of technological
projects of strategic significance to China's economic and social
progress, he said.
</P>
<P>
Talented professionals serve as the key factor for the growth
of science, technology and economy. Therefore, the social mood in
which knowledge is valued and the talents are respected should be
nurtured, Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
The state will exert more efforts to improve the working and
living conditions of intellectuals, protect intellectual property
rights and set up an incentive mechanism favorable to the talented
personnel, he said.
</P>
<P>
Li Ruihuan, who presides over the meetings of executive
chairmen of the presidium of the First Session of the Ninth CPPCC
National Committee, said at the end of the panel that the speeches
of the scientists will be collected and forwarded to relevant
departments for study and reference.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
