<HEADLINE> Social Security System in China Improves </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 4 (Xinhua) -- By the end of last year, 87.7
million employees throughout China paid into the basic retirement
program in China, the State Statistics Bureau announced at a press
conference today.
</P>
<P>
A total of 24.5 million retired pensioners joined the general
social pension system, 13 million employees joined the
general health care program for major diseases, and 1.03 million
retire pensioners joined the general health care program.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show 3.8 million people were offered unemployment
relief by labor security institutions in 1997.
</P>
<P>
To date, 41.5 percent of all townships have set up rural social
security networks, covering a rural population of 70.35 million.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
