<HEADLINE> ECOWAS Team in U.N. to Brief on S. Leone </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, March 4 (Xinhua) -- The Committee of Five on Sierra
Leone set up by the Economic Community of West African States
(ECOWAS) is in the United Nations headquarters to brief
Secretary-General Kofi Annan and the Security Council on the
latest development in that country.
</P>
<P>
The briefing will also touch on the detailed arrangements for
the successful return of elected President Ahmed Tejan Kabbah to
Sierra Leone on March 10, the Daily Champion reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The ECOWAS peacekeeping force known as ECOMOG last month
dislodged the military junta which ousted Kabbah's government
last May, paving the way for the return of the president in exile
in neighboring Guinea.
</P>
<P>
According to the report, the committee will also discuss with
Annan on the need for an early deployment of a U.N. observer
mission in war-torn Sierra Leone.
</P>
<P>
It will also emphasize the need for the international
community to urgently provide humanitarian and relief assistance
to the people of Sierra Leone.
</P>
<P>
The committee, led by Nigerian Foreign Minister Tom Ikimi,
left for the United States Tuesday.  
</P>
</TEXT>
