<HEADLINE> Chinese Population Reaches 1.236 Billion </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 4 (Xinhua) -- The total population of China was
1,236.26 million at the end of 1997, according to the latest
statistics released by China's State Statistics Bureau at a press
conference today.
</P>
<P>
The country had an urban population of 369.89 million, 29.9
percent of the total. The number of residents living in rural
areas was 866.37 million, 70.1 percent of the total.
</P>
<P>
In 1997, there were 20.83 million births and 8.01 million
deaths, with a crude birth rate of 16.57 per thousand and a crude
death rate of 6.51 per thousand.
</P>
<P>
The net growth of the population was 12.37 million, with a
natural growth rate of 10.06 per thousand.  
</P>
</TEXT>
