<HEADLINE> Investment in Basic Industry, Infrastructure Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 4 (Xinhua) -- China continued focusing on basic
industries and infrastructures in 1997, with investment in the two
sectors soaring.
</P>
<P>
According to the State Statistics Bureau (SSB), investment in
agriculture, forestry, animal husbandry, fishery and water
conservancy totalled 47 billion yuan in 1997, up 40 percent from
1996.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, investment in the energy industry shot up by 21.7
percent to 357.5 billion yuan, and that in transportation and
telecommunications sectors by 14.8 percent to 328.8 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
A SSB spokesman said at a press conference today that growth of
investment in China's western areas accelerated thanks to
government efforts to spur the local development. 
</P>
