<HEADLINE> Share Prices Continue to Drop in Tokyo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, March 4 (Xinhua) -- Stock prices fell for the second day
Wednesday in sluggish trading with no major market-moving factors.
</P>
<P>
The Nikkei average of 225 selected issues on the First Section on
the Tokyo Stock Exchange lost 72.73 points, or 0.42 percent from
Tuesday's close to 17,095.60.
</P>
<P>
The broader-based Tokyo Stock Price Index (TOPIX), covering all
issues on the First Section, finished at 1,290.92, down 5.18 points,
or 0.40 percent.
</P>
<P>
Turnover on the First Section thinned to an estimated 380 million
shares from Tuesday's 611.59 million shares.
</P>
<P>
Nippon Steel was Wednesday's most heavily traded issue.
</P>
<P>
Of the 1,329 issues listed on the First Section, losers outweighed
gainers 771 to 317, with 188 issues remaining unchanged. 
</P>
