<HEADLINE> China Witnesses Increased Production Capacities </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 4 (Xinhua) -- China today published a list of
its newly-increased production capacities through capital
construction projects in 1997.
</P>
<P>
According to a report released today by State Statistics
Bureau, China was added with annual production capacities of 25.87
million tons of coal mining, 13.76 million kw of power generation,
15.93 million tons of oil extraction, 2.1 billion cm of natural
gas extraction, 1.37 million tons of rolled steel, 880,000 tons
of chemical fertilizers, and 150,000 cm of timber felling and
transportion.
</P>
