<HEADLINE> 63 Illegal Immigrants Picked up in Zambia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, March 4 (Xinhua) -- The immigration department has in
the past 10 days picked up 63 illegal immigrants and deported 26
of them from neighboring countries, Times of Zambia reported
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The local newspaper quoted immigration spokesman Royn Miyanda
as saying here Tuesday that most of them were nabbed in Solwezi,
northwest Zambia and the capital city of Lusaka.
</P>
<P>
He said of the 63 illegal immigrants 26 from neighboring
countries have already been deported to their home countries and
the rest will also be sent back home soon.
</P>
<P>
In another development, in the past one week 48 people have
been arrested by the Drug Enforcement Commission (DEC) for
drug-related offenses and drug with a street value of 101 million
Kwacha (about 67,000 U.S. Dollars) has been seized in the
operations.
</P>
<P>
The drug seized includes 186 kilograms of marijuana, 30
kilograms of khat and 228 tablets of diazepam, according to
another local newspaper The Post.  
