<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Consensus Reached on Institutional Restructuring: NPC Spokesman </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 4 (Xinhua) -- It is high time China carried out
a government restructuring program since the current government
structure is not well adapted to a socialist market economy,
according to an NPC session spokesman here today.
</P>
<P>
Spokesman Zeng Jianhui conceded that China's government
institutions have been plagued by unwieldiness and staff
redundance. Separation of the functions of the government from
those of the enterprise has proved to be difficult, he said.
</P>
<P>
"The current government structure is ill-adapted to the need of
a socialist market economy and restructuring is,
therefore,imperative," he said.
</P>
<P>
"Conditions are now ripe for launching a restructuring program
since a consensus has been reached on the need for such a
program," he said.
</P>
<P>
One of the focal points of the upcoming NPC session is to
examine a restructuring program proposed by the State Council, he
said.
</P>
<P>
The goal of the program, he said, is to establish a highly
efficient, well-coordinated and standardized administrative
system.
</P>
<P>
Government functions will be altered to make sure that the
government will no longer be able to meddle with enterprises'
daily operation, he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
