<HEADLINE> China Makes Progress in Social Welfare </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 4 (Xinhua) -- By the end of 1997, a minimum life
guarantee system had been established in 330 Chinese cities, where
1.92 million people received minimum live guarantee relief.
</P>
<P>
According an annual report published by China's State
Statistics Bureau today, 55.32 million people received relief
funds in various forms from the state last year.
</P>
<P>
By the end of last year, there were 1.03 million beds in social
welfare institutions accommodating 790,000 inmates.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show community service network in urban areas
improved. By the year end, there were 150,000 community service
facilities, of which 5,663 were community service centers.
</P>
