<HEADLINE> Double-Tracking of Railway Line in South China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANNING, March 4 (Xinhua) -- Work has begun on a 7.7-kilometer
(km) section of a double-track railway from Luchuan to Meipo in
south China's Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region.
</P>
<P>
The project is one part of the project to double-track the
railway line running from Litang in the Guangxi region to
Zhanjiang in neighboring Guangdong Province.
</P>
<P>
At a cost of more than 400 million yuan, double-tracking of the
318-km Litang-Zhanjiang railway line has been under way
since last year and should be finished by the end of the year.
</P>
<P>
The line is believed to be the most convenient passageway
linking the country's southwest inland areas with south coastal
areas.
</P>
<P>
Along with the speedy economic development of southwest China,
the single-track Litang-Zhanjiang line cannot meet the
fast-growing traffic demand.
</P>
<P>
The double-tracking of the railway line is expected to give an
impetus to economic development in Guangxi as well as in southwest
China. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
