<HEADLINE> Qiao Shi at Presidium Meeting of Ninth NPC First Session </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 4 (Xinhua) -- "I have accomplished my mission,
and I wish this session a great success," said Qiao Shi, China's
top lawmaker in the past five years, at today's first meeting of
the Presidium of the First Session of the Ninth National People's
Congress (NPC), China's new legislature scheduled to open here
tomorrow.
</P>
<P>
As chairman of the Standing Committee of the Eighth NPC,
the 73-year-old Qiao presided over today's meeting until the
177-member Presidium elected its executive chairmen.
</P>
<P>
At 9:50 a.m., he announced: "It's now the executive chairmen's
duty to continue presiding over the Presidium meeting, and I'm
taking my leave."
</P>
<P>
The 165 Presidium members attending the meeting warmly
applauded to express their thanks to Qiao and his colleagues for
the great contributions they have made in the past five years to
improving the people's congress system as well as China's
democracy and legal system and to promoting the country's reform,
opening-up and modernization drive.
</P>
<P>
As Qiao slowly descended from the podium, Li Peng, incumbent
Chinese premier and one of the newly-elected executive chairmen of
the Presidium, rose from his seat and stepped forward and shook
hands with Qiao.
</P>
<P>
Li also shook hands with Wang Hanbin, Ni Zhifu, Chen Muhua, Fei
Xiaotong, Lei Jieqiong, Li Ximing, Wang Bingqian and Lu Jiaxi, all
vice chairmen of the Eighth NPC Standing Committee who walked down
from the podium following Qiao.
</P>
<P>
Applause burst out once again in the meeting hall.
</P>
<P>
Qiao, constantly cupping one hand in the other before his chest
in reciprocity, slowly walked out of the hall, and the meeting
went on with Li presiding.
</P>
<P>
During their term of office, Qiao and his fellow legislators
enacted a record 118 laws and relevant decisions, laying a good
foundation for the establishment of a legal system that is suited
for a socialist market economy.
</P>
<P>
They also carried out inspections on the enforcement
of 21 laws and relevant decisions, and have heard and examined 34
work reports by the State Council, the Supreme People's Court and
the Supreme People's Procuratorate.
</P>
<P>
A member of the Communist Party of China (CPC) since 1940, Qiao
was elected to the Party Central Committee at 12th CPC National
Congress in 1982.
</P>
<P>
He entered the Political Bureau of the CPC Central Committee in
1985, and was elected to the Politburo Standing Committee at
the 13th and 14th national Party congresses in 1987 and 1992.
</P>
</TEXT>
