<HEADLINE> China Increases Fixed Assets Investment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 4 (Xinhua) -- China's fixed assets investment
rose 10.1 percent in 1997 to 2.53 trillion yuan, the State
Statistics Bureau (SSB) said at a press conference today.
</P>
<P>
Of the figure, state-owned units made investment totaling
1,341.9 billion last year, up 11.3 percent from the previous year.
</P>
<P>
A breakdown of the investment indicates that China spent 986.3
billion yuan on capital construction during the year, while
investment in technical upgrading dropped 6.8 percent to 387
billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
Investment in the real estate sector fell 3.4 percent to 310.6
billion yuan. 
