<P>
Rizhao is now one of China's ten biggest ports and is one of
the world's ten largest coal ports. In recent years, it has
greatly increased its container business and has opened shipping
routes to ROK's Pusan and Japan's Osaka.
</P>
<P>
The majority of cargo from ROK to Rizhao is diesel oil,
cold-rolled steel plates, petroleum, asphalt, machines and
equipment.
</P>
<P>
Chinese exports of cement to ROK via Rizhao are growing and
amounted to more than 260,000 tons in 1997. Overseas-funded
enterprises in China contributed a great deal to cement exports to
ROK.
</P>
<P>
Other products moving between the two countries include aquatic
products, carved stone, and frozen vegetables. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
