<DOCNO> XIE19980304.0252 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Philippine Exports Continue Upsurging </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, March 4 (Xinhua) -- The Philippines' exports continued
to upsurge in January, 1998, with the revenue increasing by 24.8
percent to 2.1 billion U.S. dollars from the year-ago level, the
National Statistics Office (NSO) said here on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The NSO said in a report that electronics and components
remained the top export item, accounting for 50.5 percent of the
total receipt. Among the commodities that comprise the group,
semi-conductors garnered the biggest earning.
</P>
<P>
Input, output and peripheral units emerged as the second top
earner with receipts amounting to 163.78 million dollars, up by
62.6 percent from 100.73 million dollars in the same month last
year.
</P>
<P>
It was followed by mineral products, petroleum products and
forest products, the NSO said.
</P>
<P>
The NSO added that the United States remained as the
Philippines' top market, followed by Japan, the Netherlands,
Singapore, Britain and Germany. 
</P>
</TEXT>
