<HEADLINE> Automobile Rental Services Becoming Popular in Tianjin </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, March 4 (Xinhua) -- Automobile rentals have gained
popularity in north China's Tianjin Municipality since
September.
</P>
<P>
Local officials said four major corporations, together with
numerous small companies, are offering rental services in the
city. Automobiles for rent at these companies include Daihatsu
mini-vans and Xiali-brand cars, both manufactured in the city,
and Santana-brand cars, which are made by Shanghai Volkswagen
Corp., a Sino-German joint venture.
</P>
<P>
An overwhelming majority of the customers rent automobiles for
private purposes. A customer may rent a Daihatsu mini-van for a
day at a price of 70 yuan to 80 yuan, or spend 100 yuan or so to
rent a Xiali-brand car for a day, but Santana cars have fewer
customers as they are more expensive, said Li Fan, general manager
of the Lease Service Center of China, Agricultural Machinery
Corp., Huabei Branch.
</P>
<P>
According to Li, his center has 250 cars of 17 types for
rent. On an average day, 60 percent of the fleet is rented,
he said. But that climbs to more than 90 percent during holiday
periods.
</P>
<P>
For instance, during this year's Spring Festival, which fell on
Jan. 28-30, automobile availability at Li's center was unable to
meet demands.
</P>
<P>
Experts attributed the boom in auto leasing service to changes
in people's attitudes as Tianjin opens wider to the outside
world. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
