<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Service Sector Attracted To Southern Chinese Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, March 4 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong's service sector has
begun to move into Guangzhou, the capital of nearby Guangdong
Province, because of Guangzhou's human resources, low rents and
housing costs, management environment, and common language.
</P>
<P>
Hongkong multinationals like Cathay Pacific Airways, Hong Kong
and Shanghai Banking Corp., and Bank of East Asia have moved their
information databases and logistic support to Guangzhou, buying or
renting office buildings there.
</P>
<P>
The transfers will help regional companies lower production
costs, improve competitiveness, and help develop business in the
mainland, economists say.
</P>
<P>
The rapid development of computers has made it possible for
large businesses to separate counter services and offices, so that
finance, transport, communications, and consulting businesses can
move to major mainland cities, with Guangzhou, Shenzhen, Shanghai,
and Beijing being the favorites.
</P>
<P>
In the 1980s, Hongkong manufacturers moved a large number of
factories to the mainland, particularly the Pearl River Delta in
Guangdong Province, stimulating local economic growth, but
higher-level cooperation is now the preferred pattern. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
