<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ninth NPC First Session Presidium Holds First Meeting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 4 (Xinhua) -- The Presidium of the First Session
of the Ninth National People's Congress (NPC), which was elected
this morning, held its first meeting here today.
</P>
<P>
The meeting elected nine executive chairmen for the Presidium,
adopted group assignments for the executive chairmen, and decided
on candidates for the choice of deputy secretaries-general of the
session.
</P>
<P>
According to relevant rules of the NPC, the Presidium meeting
was presided over by Qiao Shi, chairman of the Standing Committee
of the Eighth NPC, at its beginning. On behalf of the chairman and
vice-chairmen of the Eighth NPC Standing Committee, he set forth
candidates for the posts of executive chairmen of the current
Presidium's first meeting.
</P>
<P>
The executive chairmen of the Presidium are Li Peng, Hu Jintao,
Tian Jiyun, Pagbalha Geleg Namgyai, Wang Guangying, Cheng Siyuan,
Buhe, Tomur Dawamat, and Wu Jieping.
</P>
<P>
After the executive chairmen were chosen upon recommendation,
Qiao Shi invited the executive chairman to continue to preside
over the meeting, and left the meeting hall along with Wang
Hanbin, Ni Zhifu, Chen Muhua, Fei Xiaotong, Lei Jieqiong, Li
Ximing, Wang Bingqian and Lu Jiaxi, all vice-chairmen of the
Eighth NPC Standing Committee.
</P>
<P>
The meeting, then presided over by Li Peng, adopted a draft for
bill approval procedures for the First Session of the Ninth NPC, a
draft decision on establishing special committees of the Ninth
NPC, a draft method for the Ninth NPC First Session to appoint
members of various special committees of the Ninth NPC, and the
nomination of candidates for the posts of chairman, vice-chairmen
and members of the Financial and Economic Committee of the Ninth
NPC. The drafts and the nomination will be submitted to the full
session for approval.
</P>
<P>
The drafts stipulate that approval of bills and nomination for
the special committees use an electronic voting system, and that
approval require favorable votes by more than half of all the
deputies.
</P>
<P>
The meeting decided that Cao Zhi, He Chunlin, Wang Weicheng,
Zeng Jianhui and Hu Guangbao would serve as deputy
secretaries-general of the session.
</P>
<P>
It also decided that the deadline for bill submission will be 6
p.m. on March 11. According to law, one delegation of deputies or
more than 30 deputies can jointly submit a bill to the session
within the scope of the NPC's functions and powers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
