<HEADLINE> Hundreds Feared Dead in Heavy Flood in Pakistan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, March 4 (Xinhua) -- Hundreds of people were feared
killed or missing and about 70 villages washed away on Tuesday as
heavy flood caused by torrential rains hit the Balochistan
Province, western Pakistan.
</P>
<P>
According to local news papers, the incessant rains, which
started from Monday and continued for the last 36 hours, caused
heavy loss of life and property in the Makran division of the
Balochistan, where some 60-70 villages had been either washed away
or badly damaged.
</P>
<P>
More than 75 bodies had been recovered from the running water
so far while around 250 people were still missing, said the
officials from the provincial administration.
</P>
<P>
The Public Relations Department of Balochistan said in a press
release that the flood level had broken the record of 200 years,
adding that the toll in the flood might go higher. 
</P>
</TEXT>
