<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Argentina May Have Above Normal Rainfall </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, March 3 (Xinhua) -- Argentina may have above
normal rainfall in the coming months because of the El Nino
weather phenomenon, according to a forecast by the country's
National Meteorological Service (SMN) Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Chief of Climatological Provision of the SMN Hugo Hordij said
rainfall is expected to average 130 mm in March in the country as
a whole, while the central region will receive less compared with
previous months when heavy rains hit there.
</P>
<P>
The El Nino phenomenon is the result of abnormal rises in sea
surface temperatures in the Pacific region, leading to extreme
worldwide climatic conditions such as cyclones, floods and
droughts. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
