</P>
<P>
-- With the 12th Lok Sabha (lower House) elections having
resulted in a hung parliament, the focus Tuesday night shifted
towards government formation. Both the BJP-led alliance and a
"secular front" of the Congress and the United Front were
exploring ways of enlisting support to help them cross the
272-seat rubicon.
</P>
<P>
