<HEADLINE> Myanmar to Celebrate Water Festival </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, March 4 (Xinhua) -- Myanmar leader Lieutenant-General
Tin Oo has urged its people to celebrate the forthcoming Thingyan
Water Festival (Myanmar New Year), which is to be held on an
extensive scale, in accordance with traditional culture and in a
disciplined manner.
</P>
<P>
The three-day Myanmar Water Festival is falling on April 14 to
16 in the eve of New Year according to the Myanmar calendar.
</P>
<P>
Quoting Tin Oo, second secretary of the Myanmar State Peace and
Development Council, the official New Light of Myanmar newspaper
Wednesday called on the people to celebrate the festival in a
gentle and polite way to perpetuate Myanmar life-style and
traditional culture, ensuring that there is no misbehavior nor
counter-cultural acts among merry-makers.
</P>
<P>
Preparatory measures for throwing water were discussed at a
meeting of the Yangon City Development Committee Tuesday, the
report added. 
</P>
