<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ninth NPC First Session Holds Preparatory Meeting (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 4 (Xinhua) -- The First Session of the Ninth
National People's Congress (NPC) scheduled to open here tomorrow
held its preparatory meeting today.
</P>
<P>
The meeting elected a 177-member presidium and the
secretary-general of the session.
</P>
<P>
The Presidium is composed of leaders of the Communist Party of
China (CPC) and the state, leaders of non-Communist parties and
the All-China Federation of Industry and Commerce, patriotic
personages without party affiliation, heads of the central Party,
government and military bodies and the people's organizations,
deputies from the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (SAR)
and Macao, deputies from national pillar industries and from
science and technology, social sciences, education, literature and
art, sports, public health and religious circles.
</P>
<P>
The Presidium members also include deputies representing
overseas Chinese, workers, farmers, soldiers of the People's
Liberation Army (PLA) and armed policemen, deputies from ethnic
minorities with comparatively large population, heads of
delegations to the NPC session from all provinces, autonomous
regions and municipalities directly under the central government,
and heads of the PLA delegation and the Hong Kong SAR delegation.
</P>
<P>
Tian Jiyun, vice-chairman of the Eighth NPC Standing Committee,
was elected secretary-general of the session.
</P>
<P>
Qiao Shi, chairman of the Eighth NPC Standing Committee,
presided over the meeting.
</P>
<P>
He said the First Session of the Ninth NPC is another major
event in the Chinese people's political life following the 15th
CPC National Congress convened held in September 1997.
</P>
<P>
"The successful convocation of the session is of great
importance to further encouraging and mobilizing the people of all
ethnic groups across China to hold high the great banner of Deng
Xiaoping Theory and, under the leadership of the Party Central
Committee with Jiang Zemin at the core, strive with full
confidence for an all-round advancement of the great cause of
building socialism with Chinese characteristics into the 21st
century," he added.
</P>
<P>
He described upholding Deng Xiaoping Theory and the Party's
basic line as the session's guidelines, implementing the essence
of the 15th National Party Congress comprehensively, further
emancipating the mind and seeking truth from facts, promoting a
sustained, rapid and sound growth of the national economy by
deepening reforms and expanding opening to the outside world,
promoting socialist ethical and cultural progress and improving
democracy and the legal system, and working hard with one heart
and one mind and with perseverance for an all-round advancement of
the great cause of building socialism with Chinese
characteristics.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
