<HEADLINE> Ninth NPC First Session Holds Preparatory Meeting (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The agenda of the Ninth NPC First Session approved at today's
preparatory meeting includes:
</P>
<P>
-- hearing and examining the government work report;
</P>
<P>
-- hearing, deliberating and approving a report on the
implementation of the 1997 national economic and social
development plan and a draft plan for 1998 national economic and
social development;
</P>
<P>
-- hearing, examining and approving a report on the
implementation of the 1997 central and local budgets and the draft
budgets for 1998;
</P>
<P>
-- examining a plan for institutional restructuring submitted
by the State Council;
</P>
<P>
-- hearing and examining a work report by the NPC Standing
Committee and a draft decision on establishing special committees
of the Ninth NPC;
</P>
<P>
-- hearing and examining work reports by the Supreme People's
Court and the Supreme People's Procuratorate;
</P>
<P>
-- electing chairman, vice-chairmen, secretary-general and
members of the Ninth NPC Standing Committee;
</P>
<P>
-- electing President and Vice-President of the People's
Republic of China (PRC);
</P>
<P>
-- deciding on candidates for the premiership of the State
Council and other government posts, including the posts of
vice-premiers, state councillors, heads of all ministries and
commissions, governor of the People's Bank of China,
auditor-general of the Auditing Administration, and
secretary-general of the State Council;
</P>
<P>
-- electing chairman of the Central Military Commission of the
PRC;
</P>
<P>
-- deciding on candidates for the posts of vice-chairmen and
members of the Central Military Commission of the PRC;
</P>
<P>
-- electing president of the Supreme People's Court and chief
procurator of the Supreme People's Procuratorate;
</P>
<P>
-- approving the list of candidates for the posts of
chairmen, vice-chairmen and members of all special committees
of the Ninth NPC.
</P>
<P>
The session is scheduled to run 15 days.  
</P>
