<HEADLINE> Italy, Albania Sign Aid Agreement </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, March 3 (Xinhua) -- Italy and Albania struck an agreement
here Tuesday on helping Albania rebuild its government apparatus,
a communique released by Italian Foreign Ministry said.
</P>
<P>
Italian Foreign Minister Lamberto Dini and Albanian State
Minister for Development and Economic Cooperation Ermelinda Meksi
signed the deal.
</P>
<P>
The communique said the signing brought into effect a
cooperative program in a protocol signed by Italian Foreign
Minister Lamberto Dini, in Tirana, last December.
</P>
<P>
Under the program, Italy will grant Albania 60 billion lira
(about 34 million U.S. dollars) in aid to help rebuild government
departments including the interior, justice, finance,
transportation, education, economy, agriculture and statistics.
</P>
<P>
After the signing ceremony, Dini said the agreement proved that
Italy was glad to help Albania restore stability. Meksi thanked
Italy for its aid and support. 
</P>
