<HEADLINE> Seeds Crumble in First Round of World Indoor </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, March 3 (Xinhua) -- Second seed Jonas Bjorkman of
Sweden, fourth seed Yevgeny Kafelnikov of Russia and seventh seed
Goran Ivanisevic of Croatia were crumbled in the first round of
the 725,000 U.S. dollars Rotterdam World Indoor tennis tournament
on Tuesday in Rotterdam, Netherlands.
</P>
<P>
Kafelnikov lost 7-6, 6-2 to Sweden Thomas Johansson, whom he
beat in London last week, while Ivanisevic was upset in a
three-set trounce by Dutchman Jan Siemerink, 5-7, 7-6, 6-3, which
was the third time this year for the Croatian.
</P>
<P>
And Bjorkman was stunned earlier by Spaniard Tomas Carbonel,
6-7, 6-3, 6-4.
</P>
<P>
Kafelnikov squandered a 5-2 lead in the opening set while
Johansson, ranked 34th in the world, steered up for a victory of a
baseline battle.
</P>
<P>
Ivanisevic was comfortably in the driving seat when he won the
first set and was 6-5 up when serving in the tie-break in the
second.
</P>
<P>
But Siemerink won the next two points and the set, and
eventually the match after he broke his opponent in the eighth
game in the decisive set.
</P>
<P>
Bjorkman, ranked fifth in the world, could not stop Carbonel,
who is fighting-back on the world ranking table.  The 29-year old
qualifier, whose current place is 195th, once reached as high as
40th in 1996. 
</P>
</TEXT>
