<HEADLINE> Chuan Gets Tough on Reducing Number of Generals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, March 4 (Xinhua) -- Thai Prime Minister Chuan Leekpai
has determined to reduce the number of generals in the armed
forces despite criticism, Bangkok Post reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Chuan, who is also defense minister, said he was merely
following the existing policy in making the decision.
</P>
<P>
He referred to the defense policy the country carried out in
the past five years to create a lean and efficient armed forces.
</P>
<P>
A two-page leaflet was found Monday at government house, which
blasts Chuan for his recent remarks that there were too many
generals in the armed forces.
</P>
<P>
Responding to the leaflet, Chuan said the decision to reduce
the number of generals was taken with the support of the leaders
of the three armed forces. He also vowed to do it slowly.
</P>
<P>
Chuan added that as defense minister he will seek improvements
only in areas that would be beneficial to the military. 
</P>
