<HEADLINE> UNESCO Campaigns to Preserve Tyre </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIRUT, March 3 (Xinhua) -- The United Nations Educational,
Scientific and Cultural Organization (UNESCO) Tuesday launched an
international campaign to preserve the ancient Lebanese city of
Tyre.
</P>
<P>
At a ceremony attended by Lebanese House Speaker Nabih Berry,
Cultural Minister Fawzi Hobeish and Economic and Trade Minister
Yassin Jaber, the UNESCO donated an initial 100,000 U.S. dollars
to protect the southern port city.
</P>
<P>
The scheme is expected to last 10 years and cost about 17
million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Tyre, which was listed as a world site in 1984, holds ruins
dating back as far as three centuries before Christ. But because
of natural and human factors, the city has been severely damaged
in recent decades. 
</P>
</TEXT>
