<HEADLINE> Agreement Signed for Construction of Gulei Port </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, March 4 (Xinhua) -- Two U.S. companies recently signed
an agreement with Zhangpu county in east China's Fujian province
on the construction of Gulei Port, a Grade A industrial port.
</P>
<P>
The agreement calls for China Direct Inc. and Golden Cattle
International Business Group Inc., the American partners, to carry
out first phase construction over a three year period at a cost of
1.7 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
Gulei Port, a comprehensive facility covering 10 sq.km., will
include a 200,000-ton berth, warehouse and metallurgical areas, a
power plant and a combined residential and tourism area. 
</P>
</TEXT>
