<HEADLINE> Foreign Investment Playing Bigger Role In Fujian </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, March 4 (Xinhua) -- Foreign investment has become a
major force in the 13.9 percent economic growth in east China's
Fujian Province, according to one local government official.
</P>
<P>
The official said that a one percent increase in foreign
investment can increase Fujian's gross domestic product (GDP) --
the value of goods and services -- by 0.84 percent.
</P>
<P>
The province now ranks 12th in the nation in overall economic
strength and seventh in per capita GDP. It has 22,000
foreign-backed firms, with 23 billion US dollars worth of overseas
investment, and about 30 percent of the top 100 industrial firms
in the province have been helped by foreign funds.
</P>
<P>
The technological level was also raised and nearly a half of
the technical improvement projects in the cities of Fuzhou,
Xiamen, and Quanzhou involved foreign investment.
</P>
<P>
Foreign-funded firms have also contributed to the province's
exports. In 1997, they exported 6.4 billion US dollars worth of
goods, accounting for 56 percent of the province's total. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
