<DOCNO> XIE19980304.0311 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China, Japan Jointly Release New PC </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 4 (Xinhua) -- The first product of the alliance
between Legend and Hitachi made its debut last week in Beijing,
with executives from both companies promising more to come,
today's "China Daily" reported.
</P>
<P>
Legend, China's top PC maker, and Japan-based Hitachi released
a compact PC called Wentian - meaning "probing heaven". The
alliance, established last September, has caught the attention of
the world's IT sector.
</P>
<P>
Although it looks standard and follows the Windows-Intel
structure, the new PC is noteworthy for its compact design, which
gives the impression that it integrates many characteristics of
both desktop and notebook PCs.
</P>
<P>
With monitor and host combined in a single unit, the computer
is only 19 centimeters in depth, occupying 60 percent less space
than a traditional desktop.
</P>
<P>
The computer is targeted first at customers such as financial
institutions and hotels, which need both space and quality.
</P>
<P>
The computer has an Intel 200 MHz processor and Fax/Modem card
and a self-adaptable card for accessing with the Internet. They
are two models: a 13.3-inch and a 12.1-inch.
</P>
<P>
Legend was responsible for design and integrating the
components into a workmanlike computer. Hitachi's contribution
centered on the liquid crystal screen, which is claimed to enable
high quality display, to reduce radiation - which a desktop
monitor cannot do, and to save energy by 50 percent.
</P>
<P>
This kind of screen is usually used in notebook
computers. Legend is also responsible for marketing the computer
in the Chinese market under the Legend brand and Hitachi for the
overseas market, using the Hitachi name.
</P>
<P>
Although the No.1 player in China's PC market, Legend is not in
the forefront of the world's IT development and has no foot-hold
in the production of key computer components.
</P>
<P>
Collaborating with Hitachi could allow Legend to feel the pulse
of technological advance in the world's IT industry and to prepare
for future challenges.
</P>
<P>
For Hitachi, the hope is that partnership with Legend will help
it expand production and strengthen its presence in the computer
industry, where it has limited market penetration in terms of
traditional computers. The paper said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
