<HEADLINE> Fujian-Taiwan Economic Cooperation Growing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, March 4 (Xinhua) -- East China's Fujian province,
facing Taiwan across the Taiwan Straits, has seen stable
development of economic and trade cooperation with Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
Latest statistics show that its trade volume with Taiwan
reached 2.2 billion US dollars in the firs eleven months of last
year, up 4.7 percent over the same period of the previous year.
</P>
<P>
In 1997, Fujian province approved 411 Taiwan-funded projects,
involving 1.17 billion US dollars of investment.
</P>
<P>
So far, the province has nearly 5,000 such firms involving 9.5
billion US dollars worth of Taiwan investment, and Taiwan has
become the province's second largest outside investor, after Hong
Kong.
</P>
<P>
Large Taiwan-funded projects are on the increase in the
province. The average amount of investment for each project was
5.9 million US dollars in 1997, up from less than one million US
dollars in 1988.
</P>
<P>
Agriculture has also become a major place for Fujian-Taiwan
cooperation with the establishment of two trial zones in the field.
</P>
<P>
To further promote its cooperation with Taiwan, Fujian will
adopt more preferential policies.  
</P>
</TEXT>
