<BODY>
<HEADLINE> More than 100 Sea Lions Die on Chilean Beaches </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTIAGO, March 3 (Xinhua) -- More than 100 young sea lions
have died in central and north Chile, due to the affects of the
climatic phenomenon El Nino.
</P>
<P>
The deaths were mainly attributed to food shortages because of
changes in sea conditions. High temperatures have forced some
species of marine life to change their habitats and the adult sea
lions have to leave their young to seek food. 
</P>
</TEXT>
