<HEADLINE> Ten Overseas Financial Institutions Sets Up Offices in Sichuan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, March 4 (Xinhua) -- Japan's Tokyo Marine and Fire
Insurance Co., Ltd. has set up a representative office in Chengdu,
capital of southwest China's Sichuan Province.
</P>
<P>
So far, 10 overseas financial institutions have opened offices
in the province, including the Overseas Union Bank Ltd. of
Singapore, Britain's Standard Chartered Bank and the Bank of Tokyo.
</P>
<P>
Tokyo Marine and Fire Insurance has the longest history among
the property insurance businesses in Japan and leads the world in
its total assets. It entered the Chinese market in 1980 and now
has eight representative offices and branches in China.
</P>
<P>
Overseas financial institutions have obtained approval to open
branchs and set up offices in Chengdu, which is an important
financial, transportation and culture center in southwest China.
</P>
<P>
Sichuan Province introduced 1.4 billion U.S. dollars of
contractual overseas investment in 1997, a big increase over 1996,
and issued H shares in Hong Kong to raise money for the
construction of the Chengdu-Chongqing expressway. 
</P>
</TEXT>
