<HEADLINE> Shanghai Leads Nation in Number of Financial Institutions </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, March 4 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai, China's leading
financial center, is home to 2,722 financial institutions.
</P>
<P>
Statistics released by the People's Bank of China, the nation's
central bank, show the figure includes 2,221 domestic institutions.
</P>
<P>
The municipality approved 96 financial institutions in 1997
alone. Meanwhile, 320 stock exchange handling businesses and ten
insurance firms were closed during the year, with five insurance
firms completing mergers.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai has led the nation in terms of total financial
institutions for several years running. 
</P>
