<DOCNO> XIE19980304.0327 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Poorest Area Records Steady Development </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YINCHUAN, March 4 (Xinhua) -- Xihaigu Prefecture of Northwest
China's Ningxia Hui Automonous Region, one of the country's most
impoverished area, has experienced steady development
in the past year, thanks to relief efforts by the central and local
governments.
</P>
<P>
The eight-county prefecture, occupying 30,456 square kilometers
in the southern part of the region, has suffered from erosion,
hail, frost, flood and windstorms, which seriously hampered
agricultural and industrial production.
</P>
<P>
For one thing, the region's government sent more than 3,200
cadres at all levels to the mountainous villages to help farmers
fight against natural disasters and escape poverty in 1997. For
another, the government greatly supported the prefecture's private
economy and promoted its economic cooperation with coastal areas.
</P>
<P>
In 1997, 130 million yuan was allocated to improve 20,000
hectares of farmland and dig 64,000 wells. Meanwhile, the
technology of maize plastic film was used on 32,000 hectares of
farmland, 14,000 hectares more than 1996.
</P>
<P>
As a result, the prefecture harvested 678 million kilograms of
grain in 1997. More than 200,000 farmers were able to rise above
the poverty line. This helped reduce the number of people below
poverty line in the area to half a million.
</P>
<P>
The prefecture has developed a group of township-run
enterprises and individual household-operated firms, which are
mainly engaged in processing farm-related products.
</P>
<P>
By the end of 1997, the prefecture had 45,000 private
enterprises and individual household-operated firms, which brought
in 720 million yuan of output value and sales.
</P>
<P>
To open wider to the outside, the prefecture signed more than
40 economic cooperation contracts with more than 10 provinces and
municipalities which brought in 200 million yuan of investment.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, overseas investment has boosted economic development
in this barren and mountainous area.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
