<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 0100 GMT, March 4 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW -- Andrei Kokoshin, Russia's chief military inspector,
was appointed Tuesday by President Boris Yeltsin as new head of
the nation's Security Council.
</P>
<P>
Yeltsin's spokesman Sergei Yastrzhembsky told a briefing in the
Kremlin that the Defense Council where Kokoshin served as
secretary was abolished by the president.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the Chief Military Inspectorate was integrated into
the Security Council, Yastrzhembsky said. (Russia-New Security
Secretary)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BAGHDAD -- Two planes from the United Arab Emirates (UAE) and
one from Morocco carrying relief supplies for the Iraqi people
arrived at the Saddam International Airport Tuesday, the Iraqi
News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The two UAE planes carried 80 tonnes of medicines and medical
appliances as a donation from the UAE Red Crescent Society to the
Iraqi people. (Iraq-Planeload Aid)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
ATHENS -- Greece Tuesday urged the European Union (EU) to exert
more pressure upon neighboring Turkey and northern Cyprus ahead of
the beginning of Cyprus' accession talks with the EU.
</P>
<P>
The appeal was made by Greek government spokesman Dimitris
Reppas while commenting on the recent statements by Turkish Deputy
Prime Minister Bulent Ecevit and Turkish Cypriots leader Rauf
Denktash calling for recognition of the northern Cyprus, which
unilaterally declared independent in 1983, but it has been
recognized by no countries except Turkey. (Greece-Turkey-EU)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
SEOUL -- South Korea's opposition Grand National Party (GNP)
said the cabinet members appointed Tuesday by President Kim
Dae-jung are unqualified for their posts.
</P>
<P>
Most members of the new cabinet are old faces short of
administrative experience and professional expertise needed for
their jobs, said the GNP, which occupies 161 seats at the
299-member National Assembly, or parliament.
</P>
<P>
President Kim assigned 12 of the 17 cabinet posts to members of
his National Congress for New Politics (NCNP) and its coalition
partner, the United Liberal Democrats
(ULD). (S.korea-Opposition-Cabinet)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
PARIS -- France Tuesday welcomed the newly adopted United
Nations Security Council resolution on Iraq, and sent a
presidential envoy to Baghdad in a further step to push Iraq fully
implement its agreement with U.N. Secretary-General.
</P>
<P>
French Foreign Ministry spokeswoman Anne Gazeau-Secret said
that the U.N. Resolution 1154 is "very balanced" and France is
"entirely satisfied" with it.
</P>
<P>
The spokeswoman said that the resolution "excludes any idea of
automatic strike" against Iraq if it fails to implement its
agreement with U.N. Secretary-General Kofi Annan. (France-Iraq-UN)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
ANKARA -- Turkish security forces seized 47 kilograms of pure
heroin in an operation against drug trafficking in eastern Turkey,
the semi-official Anatolia News Agency reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The agency said that acting on a tip-off, the security forces
gave a "warning" to two suspected drug smugglers near Dolucikin
village of Gurpinar town of Van province at small hours Tuesday
morning and an armed clash broke out between the security forces
and the smugglers. (Turkey-Heroin Seizure)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
LONDON-- The British company that helped to create Dolly, the
world's first cloned sheep, announced Tuesday that it has produced
the human blood clotting agent Factor IX from the milk of
transgenic sheep.
</P>
<P>
PPL Therapeutics said in a statement that the success "will be
particularly important in the light of current concerns over the
safety of products derived from human plasma."
</P>
<P>
Factor IX, which is essential in the blood clotting process,
can be used to treat haemophiliacs, who often have deficiencies in
the protein. (UK-Sheep-Human Protein)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS -- U.N. Secretary-General Kofi Annan on
Wednesday appointed Major-General Timothy Ford of Australia as
Chief of Staff of the United Nations Truce Supervision
Organization (UNTSO).
</P>
<P>
Major-General Ford will take over the command from
Major-General Rufus Modupe Kupolati of Nigeria, who will end his
tour of duty on March 31. (Annan-Appointment)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
OTTAWA -- U.S. Secretary of State Madeleine Albright will visit
Ottawa from March 9 to 10, Canadian Foreign Affairs Minister Lloyd
Axworthy announced Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
"The visit will focus on developments that have taken place in
Canada-U.S. relations since the visit of Prime Minister Jean
Chretien to Washington in April 1997," said a government news
release.
</P>
<P>
During the visit, Albright and Axworthy will discuss bilateral
issues such as Pacific salmon, environmental cooperation, and
Canada-U.S. border collaboration. (Canada-US-Visit) 
</P>
