<HEADLINE> Medical Teams Assist Nagqu Disaster Victims </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LHASA, March 4 (Xinhua) -- Local government workers and medical
teams working in the Nagqu Prefecture of the Tibet Autonomous
Region are working hard to prevent the outbreak of epidemics
resulting from the recent snow disaster.
</P>
<P>
Eight-one medical teams consisting of 274 members were sent to
Nagqu Prefecture to assist some 23,880 local victims of the disaster.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the teams, mostly from the People's Liberation
Army and People's Armed Police, are offering instructions in
emergency first aid.
</P>
<P>
local residents have suffered from snow blindness and
hypothermia as a result of blizzards which struck Nagqu beginning
in September.
</P>
<P>
The local government has allocated over 180,000 yuan (22,000 US
dollars) for medical supplies, and the regional government
provided related supplies valued a 810,000 yuan.
</P>
<P>
Charity organizations from throughout the world, including the
Red Cross Society of China, have provided substantial assistance.
</P>
<P>
The director of the Nagqu Prefectural Health Bureau said the
extensive effort will effectively prevent the outbreak of
epidemics. 
</P>
</TEXT>
