<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shanghai Witnesses Rising Obesity in Children </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, March 4 (Xinhua) -- Recent statistics show that three
out of every 100 Shanghai children under the age of six suffer
from obesity, 6.24 times the rate for only a decade ago.
</P>
<P>
Experts attribute the rise to the higher intake of calories and
carbohydrates, as well as the lack of adequate exercise.
</P>
<P>
China adopted the one-child policy some two decades
ago. Chinese parents have pampered children with affection and
allowed them to engage in overindulgence of nonnutritious foods.
</P>
<P>
Experts say the ratio of obese children will quite likely
continue to grow along with improving standards of living. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
