<HEADLINE> Ningbo to Expand Transportation Sector </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NINGBO, March 4 (Xinhua) -- Ningbo, a port city in east China's
Zhejiang Province, has adopted an ambitious plan to increase its
handling capacity for both cargo and passengers.
</P>
<P>
The plan calls for Ningbo Port to open more international
freight routes in order to increase its annual cargo handling
capacity to 87 million tons.
</P>
<P>
The port will also introduce various preferential policies to
increase its container volume.
</P>
<P>
