<HEADLINE> Malone Named NBA Player, Riley Coach of February </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, March 3 (Xinhua) -- Utah Jazz forward Karl Malone
and Miami's Pat Riley have been named the NBA Player and Coach of
the Month of February respectively.
</P>
<P>
The 11-time All-Star Malone led the Jazz a 9-2 mark in
February. He averaged 26.6 points, 10.8 rebounds and 4.0 assists
per game during the month and shot over 54 percent from the field.
</P>
<P>
Malone ranked second in scoring and eighth in rebounding among
league leaders. He scored 20 or more points in all 11 games and
scored 30 or more three times. He led the Jazz in scoring in
every contest and in rebounding nine times.
</P>
<P>
Pat Riley became the fifth coach in NBA history to win 900
games recently. He gained the 900th victory in 1,278 games,
breaking Red Auerbach's all-time record of 1,360 games.
</P>
<P>
The three-time NBA Coach of the Year guided the Heat to a
league-best 13-2 record last month.
</P>
<P>
Miami held its opponents under 100 points 13 times last month
and under 90 points 11 times in 15 outings. 
</P>
</TEXT>
