<HEADLINE> Italian Teams Win in European Basketball League </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, March 3 (Xinhua) -- Italy's three basketball teams won
all in the 1/8 round, first leg of the European basketball league
on Tuesday in Bologna, Italy.
</P>
<P>
Teamsystem Bologna fought back a steering comeback of Maccabi
Tel Aviv of Israel to win 96-93 in extra-time.
</P>
<P>
After tying at 79-79 in regular time, the Italian contenders
took their comfortable lead with 41 seconds remaining, thanks to
Carlton Myers's double three-point shot.
</P>
<P>
The American-born guard topped the game with 33 points, leading
his team for a 43-35 halftime advantage, before Doron Sheffer and
Oded Katash brought the Israelis back into the match.
</P>
<P>
Katash was the visitors' highest scorer with 32.
</P>
<P>
Kinder Bologna trounced Spain's Estudiantes 86-62, with
Yugoslav Pedrag Danilovic scored the game-high 23 points for the
home side while guard Alessandro Abbio added 18.
</P>
<P>
And Benetton Treviso completed the home teams spree, squeezing
out Slovenia's Olimpija Ljubljana 81-79.
</P>
<P>
Yugoslav pivot Zeliko Rebraca and American playmaker Henry
Williams top-scored 25 points for the team from northern Italy.
</P>
<P>
In Athens, defending champions Olympiakos was upset at home by
Partizan Belgrade of Yugaslavia, 78-74.
</P>
<P>
With European MVP Arturas Karnisovas and Dragan Tarlac on the
injury list, Olympiakos trailed all the way in the tie and
surrendered the board to their opponents.
</P>
<P>
The Greeks have to win the following two games to advance to
the quarter-finals. Olympiakos had qualified for the next round
in the last three years.
</P>
<P>
Forward Predrag Drobniak chipped in 16 points to lead the
Yugoslavs, while Deyan tomasevic added 15. 
</P>
