<HEADLINE> Shandong Lists Environmental Protection Projects </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, March 4 (Xinhua) -- East China's Shandong province plans
to complete nine ecological and environmental projects in 1998.
</P>
<P>
The projects will include controlling desertification, and
establishing nature reserves and shelterbelts around fields and
along highways, railways and river banks.
</P>
<P>
The projects will cover a total of 510,000 hectares.
</P>
<P>
Extensive local government efforts have increased Shandong's
forest coverage to 3.1 million ha. in recent years. 
</P>
</TEXT>
