<HEADLINE> Six Killed in Plane Crash in Idaho </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, March 3 (Xinhua) -- Six people were killed when a
small plane crashed in a remote area of Idaho Monday night, the
United Press International reported today.
</P>
<P>
The plane apparently caught fire after the crash near Midale,
Idaho. The twin-engine plane was reported missing Monday night
after it failed to return to the Boise airport at 6:30 p.m. MST as
scheduled.
</P>
<P>
An Idaho Army National Guard helicopter crew found the Cessna
303 northeast of the Crane Creek Reservoir in Washington County
about 10:30 a.m. MST Tuesday. The dead bodies were found in the
wreckage of the plane.
</P>
<P>
State authorities said there were six people, including four
children, on the plane.  
